
Readme

Oracle Virtual Box

https://download.virtualbox.org/virtualbox/6.1.4/VirtualBox-6.1.4-136177-Win.exe


Install Vagrant

https://www.vagrantup.com/


Go to the provisioning folder and run  

Download the vagrant folder and place it in D:\

Open the Oracle virutal box - > 

vagrant init
vagrant up

Connect to the VM using  username/password  is vagrant/vagrant      [Root password  vagrant]

If the vm creation fail with error "Virtualization need to be enabled", restart the machine and during the boot time, 
press F11/F12 and enable the virtualization from the BIOS setup.


Enable Virtualization in OS 
---------------------------

Press F2 key at startup BIOS Setup.
Press the right arrow key to the Advanced tab, Select Virtualization and then press the Enter key.
Select Enabled and press the Enter key.
Press the F10 key and select Yes and press the Enter key to save changes and Reboot into Windows.
